01:31:30.278 --> 01:31:33.156
The message you left.
By the way, Davis, how's Cynthia?

01:31:33.239 --> 01:31:36.909
- You're still seeing her, right?
- Wait, Harold. What do you mean?

01:31:36.993 --> 01:31:40.329
Excuse me. Nothing. It's good to see you.

01:31:40.413 --> 01:31:42.123
Is that Edward Towers?

01:31:43.332 --> 01:31:44.792
Wait.

01:31:45.001 --> 01:31:46.544
Davis.

01:31:47.503 --> 01:31:49.505
I'm not one to bad-mouth anyone.

01:31:49.589 --> 01:31:52.133
Your joke was amusing, but come on, man.

01:31:52.216 --> 01:31:54.677
You had one fatal flaw.

01:31:55.094 --> 01:31:57.013
Bateman is such a dork.

01:31:57.597 --> 01:32:00.683
Such a boring, spineless lightweight.

01:32:00.766 --> 01:32:04.770
Now if you said Bryce or McDermott...
Otherwise, it was amusing.

01:32:04.854 --> 01:32:07.356
Now if you'll excuse me,
I really must be going.

01:32:07.440 --> 01:32:08.774
Wait.

01:32:10.067 --> 01:32:12.195
Stop.

01:32:12.278 --> 01:32:14.197
I did it, Carnes.

01:32:15.323 --> 01:32:16.866
I killed him.

01:32:16.949 --> 01:32:19.702
I'm Patrick Bateman.

01:32:22.622 --> 01:32:24.957
I chopped Allen's fucking head off.

01:32:26.209 --> 01:32:31.130
The whole message
I left on your machine was true.

01:32:31.464 --> 01:32:34.133
Excuse me. I really must be going now.

01:32:34.800 --> 01:32:37.261
No, listen.

01:32:37.345 --> 01:32:39.972
Don't you know who I am?

01:32:40.056 --> 01:32:42.850
I'm not Davis. I'm Patrick Bateman.

01:32:45.645 --> 01:32:48.814
We talk on the phone all the time.

01:32:49.148 --> 01:32:50.816
Don't you recognise me?

01:32:52.902 --> 01:32:54.654
You're my lawyer.

01:32:56.322 --> 01:32:58.574
Now, Carnes,

01:32:58.658 --> 01:33:00.201
listen.

01:33:00.284 --> 01:33:02.495
Listen very, very carefully.

01:33:06.374 --> 01:33:08.292
I killed Paul Allen,

01:33:10.294 --> 01:33:11.796
and I liked it.

01:33:12.672 --> 01:33:15.716
I can't make myself any clearer.

01:33:15.800 --> 01:33:18.177
But that's simply not possible.

01:33:18.261 --> 01:33:19.804
And I don't find this funny any more.

01:33:19.887 --> 01:33:22.181
It never was supposed to be.

01:33:22.265 --> 01:33:24.308
- Why isn't it possible?
- It's just not.

01:33:24.392 --> 01:33:27.853
Why not, you stupid bastard?

01:33:28.354 --> 01:33:32.942
Because I had dinner with Paul Allen
twice in London, just 10 days ago.

01:33:33.025 --> 01:33:35.027
No, you...

01:33:37.697 --> 01:33:38.739
Didn't.

01:33:38.823 --> 01:33:40.825
Now, if you'll excuse me.

01:34:21.699 --> 01:34:23.868
<i>We've seen the results of that mistrust</i>

01:34:23.951 --> 01:34:27.580
<i>in the form of lies, divisions, and mistakes.</i>

01:34:27.663 --> 01:34:29.665
<i>We need to find a way to cooperate</i>

01:34:29.749 --> 01:34:32.001
<i>while realising foreign policy</i>

01:34:32.084 --> 01:34:34.670
<i>can't be run by committee.</i>

01:34:34.754 --> 01:34:37.298
<i>And I believe there's now
the growing sense</i>

01:34:37.381 --> 01:34:41.052
<i>that we can accomplish more
by cooperating.</i>

01:34:41.135 --> 01:34:45.514
<i>And, in the end, this may be
the eventual blessing in disguise</i>

01:34:45.598 --> 01:34:47.350
<i>to come out of the Iran-Contra mess</i>

01:34:47.433 --> 01:34:49.602
How can he lie like that?

01:34:51.187 --> 01:34:53.147
- How can he pull that shit?
- What shit?

01:34:53.230 --> 01:34:55.691
Now where do we have reservations at?

01:34:55.775 --> 01:34:58.194
I'm not really hungry, but I'd like
to have reservations someplace.

01:34:58.277 --> 01:35:01.197
How can you be so fucking...

01:35:01.280 --> 01:35:03.866
I don't know... Cool about it?

01:35:03.949 --> 01:35:06.535
Some guys are just born cool, I guess.

01:35:12.124 --> 01:35:13.250
Bateman?

01:35:14.502 --> 01:35:16.379
What are you so fucking zany about?

01:35:16.462 --> 01:35:19.298
I'm just a happy camper.

01:35:19.382 --> 01:35:21.050
Rockin' and a-rollin'!

01:35:22.885 --> 01:35:24.470
Oh, brother! Look.

01:35:24.553 --> 01:35:27.390
He presents himself
as this harmless old codger,

01:35:27.473 --> 01:35:29.725
but inside...

01:35:29.809 --> 01:35:31.602
But inside...

01:35:32.144 --> 01:35:34.313
<i>But inside doesn't matter.</i>

01:35:35.314 --> 01:35:39.735
Inside? Yes? Inside? Believe it or not,
Bryce, we're actually listening to you.

01:35:39.819 --> 01:35:42.446
Come on, Bateman, what do you think?

01:35:45.074 --> 01:35:46.492
Whatever.

01:35:46.575 --> 01:35:49.036
Whose moronic idea was it
to order dry beers?

01:35:49.995 --> 01:35:51.664
I need a scotch.

01:35:53.165 --> 01:35:55.626
<i>When I named him to
the U. S. Court of Appeals,</i>

01:35:55.709 --> 01:35:58.170
<i>the American Bar Association...</i>

01:36:07.555 --> 01:36:10.599
<i>There are no more barriers to cross.</i>

01:36:10.683 --> 01:36:13.185
<i>All I have in common
with the uncontrollable</i>

01:36:13.269 --> 01:36:16.272
<i>and the insane, the vicious and the evil,</i>

01:36:16.355 --> 01:36:20.109
<i>all the mayhem I have caused
and my utter indifference toward it,</i>

01:36:20.192 --> 01:36:22.528
<i>I have now surpassed.</i>

01:36:25.448 --> 01:36:28.284
<i>My pain is constant and sharp,</i>

01:36:28.367 --> 01:36:32.079
<i>and I do not hope
for a better world for anyone.</i>

01:36:32.163 --> 01:36:36.750
<i>In fact, I want my pain
to be inflicted on others.</i>

01:36:36.834 --> 01:36:39.044
<i>I want no one to escape.</i>

01:36:41.213 --> 01:36:43.340
<i>But even after admitting this,</i>

01:36:43.424 --> 01:36:45.593
<i>there is no catharsis.</i>

01:36:45.676 --> 01:36:48.429
<i>My punishment continues to elude me,</i>

01:36:48.512 --> 01:36:51.765
<i>and I gain no deeper knowledge of myself.</i>

01:36:51.849 --> 01:36:55.644
<i>No new knowledge can be
extracted from my telling.</i>

01:36:55.728 --> 01:36:59.857
<i>This confession has meant nothing.</i>
